RestTemplate inter-service calls accumulate friction:

```java
// RestTemplate approach вЂ” fragile, verbose:
public StockQuote getQuote(String symbol, String currency) {
    try {
        return restTemplate.getForObject(
            "http://market-service/api/stocks/" + symbol
                + "/quote?currency=" + currency,
            StockQuote.class);
    } catch (HttpClientErrorException.NotFound e) {
        throw new SymbolNotFoundException(symbol);
    } catch (HttpClientErrorException e) {
        throw new MarketServiceException("Error: " + e.getStatusCode());
    } catch (ResourceAccessException e) {
        throw new MarketServiceException("Market service unreachable");
    }
}

public Order placeOrder(OrderRequest req) {
    try {
        return restTemplate.postForObject(
            "http://market-service/api/orders", req, Order.class);
    } catch (Exception e) { ... }
}
// Every method: URL string building, try-catch, manual mapping
```

**With Feign Client вЂ” the whole client in a few lines:**

```java
@FeignClient(name = "market-service")
public interface MarketServiceClient {

    @GetMapping("/api/stocks/{symbol}/quote")
    StockQuote getQuote(@PathVariable String symbol,
                        @RequestParam String currency);

    @PostMapping("/api/orders")
    Order placeOrder(@RequestBody OrderRequest request);

    @GetMapping("/api/stocks")
    List<Stock> listAll();

    @DeleteMapping("/api/orders/{id}")
    void cancelOrder(@PathVariable String id);
}

// Use it вЂ” looks like a local method call:
StockQuote quote = marketServiceClient.getQuote("TCS", "INR");
Order order = marketServiceClient.placeOrder(new OrderRequest(...));
```

Spring generates the HTTP implementation at startup. No URL building. No try-catch per method. No response parsing. Same Spring MVC annotations you already know.

concept_explanation.feign_interface:
**Declaring a Feign Client interface:**

```java
import org.springframework.cloud.openfeign.FeignClient;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;
import java.util.List;

@FeignClient(name = "market-service",          // service name (matches spring.application.name)
             url = "${market.service.url}")      // URL (hardcoded until Eureka in T15.3)
public interface MarketServiceClient {

    // GET /api/stocks вЂ” returns all stocks
    @GetMapping("/api/stocks")
    List<StockDto> getAllStocks();

    // GET /api/stocks/{symbol} вЂ” path variable
    @GetMapping("/api/stocks/{symbol}")
    StockDto getStock(@PathVariable String symbol);

    // GET /api/stocks/search?q=tata&limit=10 вЂ” query parameters
    @GetMapping("/api/stocks/search")
    List<StockDto> searchStocks(@RequestParam String q,
                                 @RequestParam(defaultValue = "10") int limit);

    // POST /api/orders вЂ” request body
    @PostMapping("/api/orders")
    OrderDto placeOrder(@RequestBody PlaceOrderRequest request);

    // PUT /api/orders/{id} вЂ” path variable + body
    @PutMapping("/api/orders/{id}")
    OrderDto updateOrder(@PathVariable String id,
                          @RequestBody UpdateOrderRequest request);

    // DELETE /api/orders/{id} вЂ” path variable, void return
    @DeleteMapping("/api/orders/{id}")
    void cancelOrder(@PathVariable String id);

    // Custom headers via @RequestHeader:
    @GetMapping("/api/portfolio")
    PortfolioDto getPortfolio(@RequestHeader("X-User-Id") String userId);
}
```

**Configuration property:**
```properties
